{"title_page": "Lena (name)", "text_new": "{{infobox given name\n| name = Lena\n| image =\n| caption =\n| gender = Female\n| origin = Hebrew<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.babynames.com/name/lena|title=Lena - Meaning of name Lena at BabyNames.com|website=www.babynames.com}}</ref><br>Russian<br>Iranian<br>German<br>Greek<br>Hindi <br> Arabic\n| pronunciation = {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|l|e\u026a|n|\u0259|,_|\u02c8|l|\u025b|n|\u0259|,_|\u02c8|l|i\u02d0|n|\u0259}}\n| meaning = light / moonlight / sunlight / palm tree / generous / kind / holder of the torch\n| derived = [[Helena (given name)|Helena]], [[Magdalena (given name)|Magdalena]], -line\n| variant forms = [[Leena]], [[Leana]], [[Lina]], [[Lene]], [[Lenka (given name)|Lenka]]\n|nickname=Nana, Len, Lin, Lean {{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n}}\n\n'''Lena''' is a [[female]] [[given name]]. The name has evolved in different languages as a variation of several earlier names. In some derivations, Lena comes from the endings of Alina and [[Helen (given name)|Helena]]. Leana is seen in [[Persian language|Persian]], Hindi and Swedish, and Leena in Finnish.\n\nIn Arabic languages, it means \"generous and kind\".\n\nIn Latin, it mean \"she that allures\".\n\nIn Greek, it means \"sunlight\" and \"moonlight\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/lena#Latin|title=lena - Wiktionary|website=en.wiktionary.org}}</ref>\n\nIn Persian it means \"light\", \"sunlight\" or \"pretty girl\".\n\nIn Hebrew, it means a lady from the city of Magdala.\n\nLena was the most popular name for girls born in Poland in 2013.<ref>[http://diminutive-names.com/9-most-popular-baby-names-2013-poland-girls-boys.article Diminutive-Names.com] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140119101845/http://diminutive-names.com/9-most-popular-baby-names-2013-poland-girls-boys.article |date=2014-01-19 }}</ref>\n\n==People with the given name==\n* [[Lena (actress)]], Malayalam film actress\n* [[Lena Ackebo]] (born 1950), Swedish comic creator\n* [[Lena \u00c5kesson]] (born 1967), Swedish boxer\n* [[Lena Anderssen]], Faroese-Canadian singer-songwriter\n* [[Lena Ashwell]] (1872\u20131957), British actress\n* [[Lena Asplund]] (born 1956), Swedish politician\n*[[Lena Baker]] (1900\u20131945, American convicted of murder\n* [[Lena Bergman]] (born 1943), Swedish social services employee\n* [[Lena Bergstr\u00f6m]] (born 1961), Swedish textiles and glass designer\n* [[Lena Berntsson]] (born 1978), Swedish athlete\n* [[Lena Burke]] (born 1978), Cuban singer and actress\n* [[Lena Chamamyan]] (born 1980), Syrian singer of Armenian origin.\n* [[Lena Colburn]] (born 2010), New York School age child. Daddy's most loved girl.\n* [[Lena d'\u00c1gua]], Portuguese singer\n* [[Lena Doolin Mason]] (1864\u20131924), American Methodist preacher and poet\n* [[Lena Dunham]] (born 1986), American filmmaker and actress\n* [[Lena Erdil]] (born 1989), Turkish windsurfer\n* [[Lena Eriksson]] (born 1972), Swedish breaststroke swimmer\n* [[Lena Fiagbe]], British soul singer-songwriter\n* [[Lena Frier Kristiansen]] (born 1983), Danish badminton player\n* [[Lena Gercke]] (born 1988), German model\n* [[Lena Hallin]] (born 1961), Swedish Air Force major general\n* [[Lena H\u00e4cki]] (born 1995), Swiss biathlete\n* [[Lena Hades]] (born 1959), Russian painter\n* [[Lena Tracy Hanks]] (1879-1944), US phycologist\n* [[Lena Headey]] (born 1973), British actress\n* [[Lena Horne]]  (1917\u20132010), American singer and actress\n*[[Lena Jeger, Baroness Jeger]] (1915\u20132007), British politician\n*[[Lena Jensen]] (born 1993), Norwegian politician\n*[[Lena Jensen Rogn]] (born 1980, retired Norwegian cross-country skier.\n* [[Lena Katina]] (born 1984), Russian singer\n* [[Lena Adelsohn Liljeroth]] (born 1955), Swedish politician\n* [[Lena Lotzen]] (born 1993), German footballer\n*[[Lena Machado]] (1903\u20131974) Native Hawaiian singer, composer, and ukulele player\n*[[Lena Martell]] (born 1940), Scottish singer\n*[[Lena McEwan]] (1927\u20132011), Australian plastic surgeon\n*[[Lena McLin]] (born 1928), American composer\n*[[Lena Meyer-Landrut]] (born 1991), German singer, 2010 Eurovision Song Contest Winner\n*[[Lena Nazaryan]] (born 1983), Armenian journalist and politician\n* [[Lena Olin]] (born 1955), Swedish actress\n* [[Lena Ovchynnikova]] (born 1987), Ukrainian kickboxer and mixed martial artist\n* [[Lena Park]] (born 1976), Korean singer, also known as Park Jung Hyun (\ubc15\uc815\ud604)\n* [[Lena Philipsson]] (born 1966), Swedish singer, also known as \"Lena Ph\" \n* [[Lena Platonos]] (born 1951), Greek musician,  pianist and composer\n* [[Lena S\u00f6derberg]] (born 1951), Swedish Playboy Playmate\n* [[Lena Valaitis]] (born 1943), Lithuanian-German singer \n* [[Lena Yada]] (born 1978), Japanese-American model\n* [[Lena Zavaroni]] (1963\u20131999), Scottish singer\n* Lena Kang (born 2002), South Korean singer, member of girl group [[GWSN]]\n* [[Lena Waithe]] (born 1984) American screenwriter, producer, and actress\n* [[Leena Alam]] Afghan film, TV and theater actress\n\n===Fictional characters===\n* Lena, a fictional character played by [[Marion Cotillard]] in the 2006 film ''Toi et Moi''\n* Lena, character from ''[[Everlasting Summer]]''\n* The female protagonist in an [[Ole and Lena]] joke\n* Lenna Charlotte Tycoon, one of the main characters of ''[[Final Fantasy V]]''\n* [[Lena Adams]], character in the ''Grant County, Georgia'' series of books\n* [[Lena Kaligaris]], character in the ''Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants'' series of books\n* [[Lena Luthor]], Lex Luthor's sister in DC Comics\n* [[Lena Duchannes]], character in the ''Beautiful Creatures'' series of books\n* [[Lena Haloway]], character in the [[Delirium (Lauren Oliver novel)|''Delirium'']] series of books by Lauren Oliver\n* [[Tracer (Overwatch)|Lena \"Tracer\" Oxton]], character in the video games ''[[Overwatch (video game)|Overwatch]]'' and ''[[Heroes of the Storm]]''\n* [[Lena Seguret]], character in ''[[Les Revenants (TV series)|The Returned]]'' television show\n* [[Lena Younger]], character in the ''[[A Raisin In The Sun]]'' play\n* Lena, character in the book series ''[[Fablehaven]]''\n* [[Magica De Spell#DuckTales familiars|Lena De Spell]], character in the ''[[DuckTales (2017 TV series)|DuckTales]]'' television show.\n\n==People with the surname==\n*[[Jeffrey Lena]] (born 1958), American lawyer\n*[[Jennie Lena]], Dutch singer-songwriter\n*[[Nijaz Lena]] (born 1986), Macedonian footballer\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{given name|type=both}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lena (name)}}\n[[Category:Czech feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Russian feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Scandinavian feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Slovak feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Indian feminine given names]]\n[[Category:German feminine given names]]\n[[Category:English feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Greek feminine given names]]\n[[Category:French feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Spanish feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Swedish feminine given names]]\n[[Category:Polish feminine given names]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox given name\n| name = Lena\n| image =\n| caption =\n| gender = Female\n| origin = Hebrew<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.babynames.com/name/lena|title=Lena - Meaning of name Lena at BabyNames.com|website=www.babynames.com}}</ref><br>Russian<br>Iranian<br>German<br>Greek<br>Hindi <br> Arabic\n| pronunciation = {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|l|e\u026a|n|\u0259|,_|\u02c8|l|\u025b|n|\u0259|,_|\u02c8|l|i\u02d0|n|\u0259}}\n| meaning = light / moonlight / sunlight / palm tree / generous / kind / holder of the torch\n| derived = [[Helena (given name)|Helena]], [[Magdalena (given name)|Magdalena]], -line\n| variant forms = [[Leena]], [[Leana]], [[Lina]], [[Lene]], [[Lenka (given name)|Lenka]]\n|nickname=Nana, Len, Lin, Lean {{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n}}\n\n'''Lena''' is a [[female]] [[given name]]. The name has evolved in different languages as a variation of several earlier names. In some derivations, Lena comes from the endings of Alina and [[Helen (given name)|Helena]]. Leana is seen in [[Persian language|Persian]], Hindi and Swedish, and Leena in Finnish.\n\nIn Arabic languages, it means \"generous and kind\".\n\nIn Latin, it mean \"she that allures\".\n\nIn Greek, it means \"sunlight\" and \"moonlight\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/lena#Latin|title=lena - Wiktionary|website=en.wiktionary.org}}</ref>\n\nIn Persian it means \"light\", \"sunlight\" or \"pretty girl\".\n\nIn Hebrew, it means a lady from the city of Magdala.\n\nLena was the most popular name for girls born in Poland in 2013.<ref>[http://diminutive-names.com/9-most-popular-baby-names-2013-poland-girls-boys.article Diminutive-Names.com] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140119101845/http://diminutive-names.com/9-most-popular-baby-names-2013-poland-girls-boys.article |date=2014-01-19 }}</ref>\n\n==People with the given name==\n* [[Lena (actress)]], Malayalam film actress\n* [[Lena Ackebo]] (born 1950), Swedish comic creator\n* [[Lena \u00c5kesson]] (born 1967), Swedish boxer\n* [[Lena Anderssen]], Faroese-Canadian singer-songwriter\n* [[Lena Ashwell]] (1872\u20131957), British actress\n* [[Lena Asplund]] (born 1956), Swedish politician\n*[[Lena Baker]] (1900\u20131945, American convicted of murder\n* [[Lena Bergman]] (born 1943), Swedish social services employee\n* [[Lena Bergstr\u00f6m]] (born 1961), Swedish textiles and glass designer\n* [[Lena Berntsson]] (born 1978), Swedish athlete\n* [[Lena Burke]] (born 1978), Cuban singer and actress\n* [[Lena Chamamyan]] (born 1980), Syrian singer of Armenian origin.\n* [[Lena d'\u00c1gua]], Portuguese singer\n* [[Lena Doolin Mason]] (1864\u20131924), American Methodist preacher and poet\n* [[Lena Dunham]] (born 1986), American filmmaker and actress\n* [[Lena Erdil]] (born 1989), Turkish windsurfer\n* [[Lena Eriksson]] (born 1972), Swedish breaststroke swimmer\n* [[Lena Fiagbe]], British soul singer-songwriter\n* [[Lena