n|SI         = {{convert|2556.5|m/s|isp|abbr=on}}\n|burntime   = 158 seconds\n|fuel       = [[N2O4|N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>4</sub>]] / [[UDMH]]\n}}\n{{Infobox rocket/stage\n|type       = stage\n|stageno    = Second\n|length     = {{convert|12.92|m|abbr=on}}\n|diameter   = {{convert|3.35|m|abbr=on}}\n|empty      = <!--{{convert|5000|kg}}-->\n|gross      = <!--{{convert|55000|kg}}-->\n|propmass   = {{convert|49400|kg|abbr=on}}\n|engines    = 1 [[YF-20|YF-24E]] (YF-22E (Main)<br/>4 x YF-23C (Vernier))\n|thrust     = {{convert|742|kN|abbr=on}} (Main)<br/>{{convert|47.1|kN|abbr=on}} (Vernier)\n|SI         = {{convert|2922.57|m/s|isp|abbr=on}} (Main)<br/>{{convert|2910.5|m/s|isp|abbr=on}} (Vernier)\n|burntime   = 185 seconds\n|fuel       = [[N2O4|N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>4</sub>]] / [[UDMH]]\n}}\n{{Infobox rocket/stage\n|type       = stage\n|stageno    = Third\n|length     = {{convert|12.38|m|abbr=on}}\n|diameter   = {{convert|3.0|m|abbr=on}}\n|empty      = <!--{{convert|2800|kg}}-->\n|gross      = <!--{{convert|21000|kg}}-->\n|propmass   = {{convert|18200|kg|abbr=on}}\n|engines    = 1 [[YF-75]]\n|thrust     = {{convert|167.17|kN|abbr=on}}\n|SI         = {{convert|4295|m/s|isp|abbr=on}}\n|burntime   = 478 seconds\n|fuel       = [[LH2|LH<sub>2</sub>]] / [[LOX]]\n}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Long March 3C''' ({{zh|s=\u957f\u5f81\u4e09\u53f7\u4e19\u706b\u7bad|t=\u9577\u5f81\u4e09\u865f\u4e19\u706b\u7bad|p=Ch\u00e1ngzh\u0113ng S\u0101nh\u00e0o B\u01d0ng Hu\u01d2ji\u00e0n}}), also known as the '''Changzheng 3C''', '''CZ-3C''' and '''LM-3C''', is a Chinese [[orbit]]al [[carrier rocket]]. It is launched from Launch Complex 2 and 3 at the [[Xichang Satellite Launch Center]]. A 3-stage rocket with two strapon [[liquid rocket boosters]], it is a member of the [[Long March 3 rocket family]], and was derived from the [[Long March 3B]]. It was designed to fill a gap in payload capacities between the [[Long March 3A]] and [[Long March 3B|3B]].\n\n==Launches==\nIt made its maiden flight on 25 April 2008, at 15:35 UTC. The payload for the first launch was the [[Tianlian-1]] data relay [[communications satellite]]. The second carried the [[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G2]] navigation satellite and was conducted on 14 April 2009. The third launch was made on 16 January 2010, with the [[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G1]] satellite. The fourth carrying the [[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G3]] navigation satellite was launched on 2 June 2010. On 1 October 2010, it successfully launched China's second lunar probe, [[Chang'e 2]].\n\nAn enhanced version of the Long March 3C rocket debuted during the launch of [[Chang'e 5-T1]] on 23 October 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barbosa|first1=Rui C.|title=China launches lunar sample return test mission|url=http://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2014/10/china-lunar-sample-return-test-mission/|publisher=[[NASASpaceflight.com]]|date=23 October 2014|accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref> On 30 March 2015, the [[Yuanzheng-1]] upper stage was used on top of a Long March 3C rocket for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barbosa|first1=Rui C.|title=Long March 3C in secretive launch with new Upper Stage |url=http://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2015/03/long-march-3c-launch-new-upper-stage/|publisher=NASASpaceflight.com|date=30 March 2015|accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==List of launches==\n{{main|List of Long March launches}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" <!--border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 0em 0.5em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"-->\n|----- style=\"background:#FFDEAD;\"\n! Flight number\n! Date (UTC)\n! Launch site\n! Version\n! Payload\n! Orbit\n! Result\n|-\n|1\n|April 25, 2008<br />15:35\n|[[Xichang Launch Area 2|LA-2]], [[Xichang Satellite Launch Center|XSLC]]\n|3C\n|[[Tianlian I-01]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|2\n|April 14, 2009<br />16:16\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G2]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|3\n|January 16, 2010<br />16:12\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G1]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|4\n|June 2, 2010<br />15:53\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G3]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|5\n|October 1, 2010<br />10:59\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[Chang'e 2]]\n|[[Lunar transfer orbit|LTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|6\n|October 31, 2010<br />16:26\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G4]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|7\n|July 11, 2011<br />15:41\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[Tianlian I-02]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|8\n|February 24, 2012<br />16:12\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G5]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|9\n|July 25, 2012<br />15:43\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[Tianlian I-03]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|10\n|October 25, 2012<br />15:33\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G6]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|11\n|October 23, 2014<br />18:00\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C/E\n|[[Chang'e 5-T1]]\n|[[Lunar transfer orbit|LTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|12\n|March 30, 2015<br />13:52\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C/[[Yuanzheng-1|YZ-1]]\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|BDS I1-S]]\n|[[Geosynchronous orbit|GSO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|13\n|February 1, 2016<br />07:29\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C/[[Yuanzheng-1|YZ-1]]\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|BDS M3-S]]\n|[[Medium Earth orbit|MEO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|14\n|June 12, 2016<br />15:30\n|[[Xichang Launch Area 3|LA-3]], XSLC\n|3C/E\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G7]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|15\n|November 22, 2016<br />15:24\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C/E\n|[[Tianlian I-04]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|16\n|December 24, 2018<br />16:53\n|LA-3, XSLC\n|3C/E\n|[[TJSW-3]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|17\n|May 17, 2019<br />15:48\n|LA-2, XSLC\n|3C/E\n|[[BeiDou Navigation Satellite System|Compass-G8]]\n|[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n|{{Success}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Portal|Spaceflight|China}}\n{{Long March rockets}}\n{{Expendable launch systems}}\n{{CLEP}}\n\n{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n\n[[Category:Long March (rocket family)]]\n[[Category:Vehicles introduced in 2008]]\n\n\n{{rocket-stub}}\n{{PRChina-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox rocket\n|image          = Image:CZ-3C.svg \n|caption        = Drawing of Long March 3C\n|function       = [[Carrier rocket]]\n|manufacturer   = [[China Academy of Launch Vehicle Technology|CALT]]\n|country-origin = China \n|status         = Active\n|sites          = [[Xichang Launch Area 2|LA-2]] and [[Xichang Launch Area 3|LA-3]], [[Xichang Satellite Launch Center|XSLC]]\n|height         = {{convert|54.8|m|ft}} <ref name=\"EA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/cz3c.htm|title=CZ-3C|author=Mark Wade|publisher=[[Encyclopedia Astronautica]]|accessdate=2008-04-26|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080601181331/http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/cz3c.htm|archivedate=2008-06-01}}</ref>\n|diameter       = {{convert|3.35|m|ft}} <ref name=\"EA\"/>\n|mass           = {{convert|345000|kg|lb}} <ref name=\"EA\"/>\n|stages         = 3\n|launches       = 17<!-- UPDATE after each launch -->\n|success        = 17<!-- UPDATE after each launch -->\n|first          = 25 April 2008\n|last           = <!-- UPDATE after each launch -->\n|capacities     = \n  {{Infobox Rocket/Payload\n  |location=[[Geosynchronous transfer orbit|GTO]]\n  |kilos     = '''3C:''' {{convert|3800|kg|lb}} <ref name=\"CGWIC_User_Manual\">{{cite web|url=http://www.