er Lee]]<ref name=\"Horror News\" />\n* [[Bela Lugosi]]<ref name=\"Horror News\"/>\n* [[Bill Moseley]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.trulydisturbing.com/2018/04/07/horror-icon-month-bill-moseley-2/ | title=HORROR ICON OF THE MONTH: BILL MOSELEY | date=April 7, 2018 | website=Truly Disturbing}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/philip-anselmo-and-horror-icon-bill-moseley-dirty-eye-video/ | title=PHILIP ANSELMO And Horror Icon BILL MOSELEY: 'Dirty Eye' Video | date=May 4, 2017 | website=Blabbermouth.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Looking Back at Horror Icon Bill Moseley\u2019s 10 Most Memorable Roles | url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/editorials/3582461/10-memorable-bill-moseley-roles/ | date=September 16, 2019 | access-date=September 16, 2019 | website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] | author=Meagan Navarro}}</ref>\n* [[Vincent Price]]<ref>{{cite book|last1=Clark|first1=Mark|title=Smirk, Sneer and Scream: Great Acting in Horror Cinema|date=2004|publisher=McFarland & Company|isbn=0786419326|pages=100, 102|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y8MtgnIj5VQC&pg=PA102&dq=%22Horror+icon%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=9gMlVMKlCpCryASD3oLIDA&ved=0CDIQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=%22Horror%20icon%22&f=false|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Barbara Steele]]<ref>{{cite book|last1=Chibnall|first1=Steve|last2=Petley|first2=Julian|title=British Horror Cinema|date=2001|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=9780415230032|page=83|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H21BB8SZuyQC&pg=PA83&dq=%22Horror+icon%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=9gMlVMKlCpCryASD3oLIDA&ved=0CEkQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=%22Horror%20icon%22&f=false|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Angus Scrimm]]<ref name=\"Horror News\"/>\n* [[Tony Todd]]<ref name=\"Horror News\"/>\n\n====Make-up artists====\n* [[Tom Savini]]<ref>https://movieweb.com/trick-or-treat-studios-tom-savini-zombie-masks/</ref>\n\n===Fictional===\n====Characters====\n* [[Ash Williams]]\n* [[Candyman (character)|Candyman]]<ref name=Remake>{{cite book|last1=Francis, Jr.|first1=James|title=Remaking Horror: Hollywood's New Reliance on Scares of Old|date=2013|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786470884|page=52|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EG58HMvheVgC&pg=PA36&dq=%22Horror+icon%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JQglVOO2Lsqm8QGjp4GwDg&ved=0CBwQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=%22Horror%20icon%22&f=false|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Chucky (character)|Chucky]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Dracula]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Frankenstein's monster]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Freddy Krueger]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Gill-man]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Hannibal Lecter]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Harry Warden]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Jason Voorhees]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Jigsaw (Saw character)|Jigsaw]]\n* [[Leatherface]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Michael Myers (Halloween)|Michael Myers]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[It (character)|Pennywise the Dancing Clown]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Pinhead (Hellraiser)|Pinhead]]<ref name=Remake/>\n* [[Sadako Yamamura]]\n* [[Tiffany Valentine]]<ref>https://bloody-disgusting.com/videos/3573897/video-new-fan-film-tiffany-chucky-imagines-two-horror-icons-might-met/</ref>\n\n====Figures====\n* [[Annabelle_(film)|Annabelle]], inanimate porcelain doll from the \"conjuring\" and \"Annabelle\" franchises.\n* [[Billy the Puppet]], inanimate puppet from the ''Saw'' franchise\n* [[Ghostface (identity)|Ghostface]], identity used by several characters in the ''Scream'' franchise.\n* [[The Mummy (franchise)|The Mummy]], stock figure in horror films<ref name=\"book 1\"/>\n\n====Creatures====\n* [[Zombies in popular culture|Zombies]]\n* [[Vampire]]s\n* [[Werewolves]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Scream queen]]\n* [[Cultural icon]]\n* [[Horror Hall of Fame]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite journal|last1=Diego|first1=Catherine Don|title=Hits, whacks, and smokes: The celluloid Gangster as horror icon|journal=Post Script|date=Summer 2002|volume=21|issue=3|pages=87\u2013100|url=http://go.galegroup.com/ps/i.do?id=GALE%7CA95501720&v=2.